YELLOW FEVER - BRAZIL: VACCINE DEATHS
*************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Yellow fever vaccine - Brazil 20000202154105
Yellow fever vaccination - Brazil 20000315093510
Yellow fever - Brazil (Brasilia ex W.Central)(03) 20000324230732
Date: Sat, 25 Mar 2000 15:01:57 -0300
From: Luiz Jacintho da Silva <luiz_jacintho@uol.com.br>

Re:
> When you vaccinate 32 million people, somebody is sure to die shortly
> afterwards by simple random chance. I have not seen any evidence that the
> unfortunate person died of yellow fever. - Mod.JW
Both deaths from yellow fever vaccination were due to the vaccine itself.
Both patients died from a typical clinical and pathological case of yellow
fever. A post-mortem was conducted in both cases, and in both yellow fever
was confirmed. Yellow fever virus grew in blood and tissues in both cases.
Again in both cases the virus was demonstrated to be the vaccine virus, not
a wild one.
I agree that the vaccine still boasts an excellent curriculum vitae of
safety, but, in the case of Sao Paulo, the risk/benefit equation suffered
a change, and mass vaccination was interrupted.
--
Luiz Jacintho da Silva
ProMED-PORT Moderator
e-mail: ljsilva@sucen.sp.gov.br
